  <div class="one-third column">
    <h4 class="myheadings">PARTY Mode &gt;&gt;</h4>
    <div class="thecontent">
      <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V375</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V475</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V500D</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V575</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V675</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V775</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V1075</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V2073</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>PARTY Mode activates all zones to run the same source audio, regardless of whether this is a digital or analogue source.</p>
      <p>There is also universal volume control for those zones meaning the volume will adjust in all zones at the same time. Users can adjust the zones that are activated when PARTY Mode is turned on.</p>
      <p align="center"><img src="images/party-mode.jpg" ></p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="myheadings">Intelligent Amplifier Assignment &gt;&gt;</h4>
    <div class="thecontent">
      <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V375</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V475</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V500D</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V575</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V675</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V775</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V1075</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V2073</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>With additional speaker terminals on Yamaha’s multi-zone receivers, users can connect 7 speakers in the main zone and additional 2 speakers in Zone 2/3.</p>
      <p>When Zone 2 is activated on a 7 channel amplifier it re-assigns two internal amplifiers from the surround back channels to Zone 2. With a 9 channel amplifier this is done when Zone 3 is activated. When the Zone is turned off, the amplifiers are automatically assigned to the surround back channels.</p>
      <p><img src="images/intelligent.jpg" width="100%" ></p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="myheadings">Zone 2 Component Video &gt;&gt;</h4>
    <div class="thecontent">
      <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V375</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V475</td>
